37const int kMaxTurnUsernameLength = 509; // RFC 8489 section 14.3
38
39extern const int STUN_ATTR_TURN_LOGGING_ID;
40extern const char TURN_PORT_TYPE[];
41class TurnAllocateRequest;
42class TurnEntry;
43
44class TurnPort : public Port {
45 public:
46 enum PortState {
47 STATE_CONNECTING, // Initial state, cannot send any packets.
48 STATE_CONNECTED, // Socket connected, ready to send stun requests.
49 STATE_READY, // Received allocate success, can send any packets.
50 STATE_RECEIVEONLY, // Had REFRESH_REQUEST error, cannot send any packets.
51 STATE_DISCONNECTED, // TCP connection died, cannot send/receive any
52 // packets.
53 };
54 // Create a TURN port using the shared UDP socket, |socket|.
55 static std::unique_ptr<TurnPort> Create(
56 rtc::Thread* thread,
57 rtc::PacketSocketFactory* factory,
58 rtc::Network* network,
59 rtc::AsyncPacketSocket* socket,
60 const std::string& username, // ice username.
61 const std::string& password, // ice password.
62 const ProtocolAddress& server_address,
63 const RelayCredentials& credentials,
64 int server_priority,
65 const std::string& origin,
66 webrtc::TurnCustomizer* customizer) {
67 // Do basic parameter validation.
68 if (credentials.username.size() > kMaxTurnUsernameLength) {
69 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Attempt to use TURN with a too long username "
70 << "of length " << credentials.username.size();
71 return nullptr;
72 }
73 // Do not connect to low-numbered ports. The default STUN port is 3478.
74 if (!AllowedTurnPort(server_address.address.port())) {
75 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Attempt to use TURN to connect to port "
76 << server_address.address.port();
77 return nullptr;
78 }
79 // Using `new` to access a non-public constructor.
80 return absl::WrapUnique(new TurnPort(
81 thread, factory, network, socket, username, password, server_address,
82 credentials, server_priority, origin, customizer));
83 }
84 // TODO(steveanton): Remove once downstream clients have moved to |Create|.
85 static std::unique_ptr<TurnPort> CreateUnique(
86 rtc::Thread* thread,
87 rtc::PacketSocketFactory* factory,
88 rtc::Network* network,
89 rtc::AsyncPacketSocket* socket,
90 const std::string& username, // ice username.
91 const std::string& password, // ice password.
92 const ProtocolAddress& server_address,
93 const RelayCredentials& credentials,
94 int server_priority,
95 const std::string& origin,
96 webrtc::TurnCustomizer* customizer) {
97 return Create(thread, factory, network, socket, username, password,
98 server_address, credentials, server_priority, origin,
99 customizer);
100 }
101
102 // Create a TURN port that will use a new socket, bound to |network| and
103 // using a port in the range between |min_port| and |max_port|.
104 static std::unique_ptr<TurnPort> Create(
105 rtc::Thread* thread,
106 rtc::PacketSocketFactory* factory,
107 rtc::Network* network,
108 uint16_t min_port,
109 uint16_t max_port,
110 const std::string& username, // ice username.
111 const std::string& password, // ice password.
112 const ProtocolAddress& server_address,
113 const RelayCredentials& credentials,
114 int server_priority,
115 const std::string& origin,
116 const std::vector<std::string>& tls_alpn_protocols,
117 const std::vector<std::string>& tls_elliptic_curves,
118 webrtc::TurnCustomizer* customizer,
119 rtc::SSLCertificateVerifier* tls_cert_verifier = nullptr) {
120 // Do basic parameter validation.
121 if (credentials.username.size() > kMaxTurnUsernameLength) {
122 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Attempt to use TURN with a too long username "
123 << "of length " << credentials.username.size();
124 return nullptr;
125 }
126 // Do not connect to low-numbered ports. The default STUN port is 3478.
127 if (!AllowedTurnPort(server_address.address.port())) {
128 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Attempt to use TURN to connect to port "
129 << server_address.address.port();
130 return nullptr;
131 }
132 // Using `new` to access a non-public constructor.
133 return absl::WrapUnique(
134 new TurnPort(thread, factory, network, min_port, max_port, username,
135 password, server_address, credentials, server_priority,
136 origin, tls_alpn_protocols, tls_elliptic_curves,
137 customizer, tls_cert_verifier));
138 }
139 // TODO(steveanton): Remove once downstream clients have moved to |Create|.
140 static std::unique_ptr<TurnPort> CreateUnique(
141 rtc::Thread* thread,
142 rtc::PacketSocketFactory* factory,
143 rtc::Network* network,
144 uint16_t min_port,
145 uint16_t max_port,
146 const std::string& username, // ice username.
147 const std::string& password, // ice password.
148 const ProtocolAddress& server_address,
149 const RelayCredentials& credentials,
150 int server_priority,
151 const std::string& origin,
152 const std::vector<std::string>& tls_alpn_protocols,
153 const std::vector<std::string>& tls_elliptic_curves,
154 webrtc::TurnCustomizer* customizer,
155 rtc::SSLCertificateVerifier* tls_cert_verifier = nullptr) {
156 return Create(thread, factory, network, min_port, max_port, username,
157 password, server_address, credentials, server_priority,
158 origin, tls_alpn_protocols, tls_elliptic_curves, customizer,
159 tls_cert_verifier);
160 }
